gov.va.vinci.leo.listener

Class BaseCsvListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.uima.aae.client.UimaAsBaseCallbackListener
      • gov.va.vinci.leo.listener.BaseListener
        • gov.va.vinci.leo.listener.BaseCsvListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.apache.uima.aae.client.UimaASStatusCallbackListener
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SimpleCsvListener

    public abstract class BaseCsvListener
extends BaseListener
    Base gov.va.vinci.leo.listener for creating CSV output. Implementing classes need to implement getHeaders() and getRows().

    If not overridden in the constructors, the default separator is a comma (,), the default quote character is a quote("), the default escape character is a backslash (\), and the default line ending is a newline (\n)

    • Method Detail

      • getRows

        protected abstract List<String[]> getRows(org.apache.uima.cas.CAS cas)
        Given a cas, return one or more rows of data.
        Parameters:
        cas - the document cas to get results from
        Returns:
        A list of rows of CSV data. Each row is an array of strings. If no data needs to be written for this CAS, you should return an empty list.

      • getHeaders

        protected abstract String[] getHeaders()
        Returns the string list of the headers for a row. ie ("col1", "id", "myValue");
        Returns:
        the string list of the headers for a row.

      • writeHeaders

        public void writeHeaders()
                  throws IOException
        Write out headers to the writer for this gov.va.vinci.leo.listener. The idea being this might be called once before the process is started to write out column headers to the csv file.
        Throws:
        IOException - if the headers cannot be written.
